<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1626,1974]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis box="[151,283,1628,1651]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Description</emphasis>
: Male length (N= 
<number box="[496,510,1626,1650]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
) (including tegmen): 5.0–5.1 mm, length of tegmen: 4.5–4.6mm; female length (N= 
<number box="[198,211,1662,1686]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
) (including tegmen): 5.6–5.8 mm, length of tegmen: 5.0–5.2mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1626,1974]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis box="[199,336,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Colouration</emphasis>
: General colour pale yellow (one male specimen pale greenish yellow). Vertex pale yellow. Eyes dark brown. Frons dark brown with yellowish green fascia near clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1100,1734,1758]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[166,1415,243,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,213,1844]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 19. adult, dorsal view; 20. head and thorax, dorsal view; 21. adult, lateral view; 22. frons and clypeus; 23. tegmen; 24. wing. Scale bars = 1 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211931/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1068,1100,1734,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Frontoclypeal suture black. Clypeus fusco-piceous. Rostrum yellow brown. Antenna brown. Pronotum pale yellow and suffused with black near posterior margin medially. Mesonotum pallid greenish yellow with or without a blackish stripe medially. Tegmen translucent, pale yellow at base, with four marks: two wide oblique black stripes at basal third and apical third, one short, narrow, oblique stripe at middle of post marginal portion, one black spot at apical third of tegmen (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[166,1415,243,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,213,1844]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 19. adult, dorsal view; 20. head and thorax, dorsal view; 21. adult, lateral view; 22. frons and clypeus; 23. tegmen; 24. wing. Scale bars = 1 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211931/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Figs. 
<number box="[151,225,1914,1938]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="21.23">21, 23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wing light brown, veins hazel with dark microtrichia (
<figureCitation box="[853,937,1914,1938]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[166,1415,243,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,213,1844]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 19. adult, dorsal view; 20. head and thorax, dorsal view; 21. adult, lateral view; 22. frons and clypeus; 23. tegmen; 24. wing. Scale bars = 1 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211931/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[905,937,1914,1938]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs yellow brown, apices of teeth of hind legs black.
</paragraph>
