<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1598]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis box="[199,386,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Head and thorax</emphasis>
: Vertex wide, anterior margin straight, posterior margin slightly concave, 3.3 times wider than long in midline, disc distinctly depressed (
<figureCitation box="[629,768,186,210]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[166,1415,243,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,213,1844]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 19. adult, dorsal view; 20. head and thorax, dorsal view; 21. adult, lateral view; 22. frons and clypeus; 23. tegmen; 24. wing. Scale bars = 1 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211931/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[693,768,186,210]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="19.2">19, 20</number>
</figureCitation>
). Frons broad with numerous punctures, 1.4 times wider at widest part than at base, lateral margin distinctly elevated (
<figureCitation box="[830,916,221,245]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[166,1415,243,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,213,1844]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 19. adult, dorsal view; 20. head and thorax, dorsal view; 21. adult, lateral view; 22. frons and clypeus; 23. tegmen; 24. wing. Scale bars = 1 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211931/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[885,916,221,245]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Frontoclypeal suture approximately straight. Clypeus relatively small, slightly depressed at basal third, disc prominent. Rostrum attaining post-trochanters. Pronotum anterior margin produced between eyes, posterior margin straight medially, disc slightly concave with minute punctures. Mesonotum triangular and wrinkled, 2.1 times wider at widest part than long (
<figureCitation box="[1206,1288,325,349]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[166,1415,243,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,213,1844]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 19. adult, dorsal view; 20. head and thorax, dorsal view; 21. adult, lateral view; 22. frons and clypeus; 23. tegmen; 24. wing. Scale bars = 1 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211931/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[1257,1288,325,349]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tegmen 1.6 times longer than widest part (
<figureCitation box="[496,636,359,383]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[166,1415,243,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,213,1844]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 19. adult, dorsal view; 20. head and thorax, dorsal view; 21. adult, lateral view; 22. frons and clypeus; 23. tegmen; 24. wing. Scale bars = 1 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211931/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[561,636,359,383]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="21.23">21, 23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wing with veins lightly reticulate, veins with minute setae, 0.7 times length of tegmen, 2.3 times longer than widest part (
<figureCitation box="[722,804,394,418]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[166,1415,243,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,213,1844]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 19. adult, dorsal view; 20. head and thorax, dorsal view; 21. adult, lateral view; 22. frons and clypeus; 23. tegmen; 24. wing. Scale bars = 1 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211931/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[773,804,394,418]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Spinal formula of hind leg 
<date box="[1118,1201,394,419]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1914-07-03">
<number box="[1118,1139,395,419]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="3.0">3</number>
<number box="[1145,1201,394,418]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="10.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="7.0">7–14</number>
</date>
– 
<number box="[1216,1230,394,418]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2.0">2</number>
, Ƥ 
<date box="[1268,1358,394,418]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1916-09-02">
<number box="[1268,1325,394,418]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="12.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="9.0">9–16</number>
– 
<number box="[1340,1354,394,418]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2.0">2</number>
.
</date>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1598]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis box="[199,363,429,453]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Anal tube nearly triangle in dorsal view and narrow at base, widest at apical part, apical margin convex at middle, with one angulate prominence on each side, and middle part concave (
<figureCitation box="[1137,1221,463,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[199,1394,178,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1405,177,1866]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 38 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 25. male anal tube, dorsal view; 26. aedeagus, right view; 27. female anal tube, dorsal view; 28. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, ventral view; 29. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, right view; 30. capitulum, dorsal view; 31. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, dorsal view; 32. gonoplac, dorsal view; 33. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, right view; 34. gonoplac, left view; 35. sternum VII; 36. aedeagus, left view; 37. apex of aedeagus, ventral view; 38. male genitalia, left view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211932/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[1189,1221,463,487]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Anal column narrow and short (about 0.1 times as long as anal tube). Suspensorium narrow, with faintly pigmented median field. Pygofer with dorsolateral angles not developed, posterior margin obtusely projecting medially, anterior margin shallowly concave in upper half (
<figureCitation box="[529,614,567,591]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[199,1394,178,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1405,177,1866]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 38 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 25. male anal tube, dorsal view; 26. aedeagus, right view; 27. female anal tube, dorsal view; 28. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, ventral view; 29. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, right view; 30. capitulum, dorsal view; 31. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, dorsal view; 32. gonoplac, dorsal view; 33. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, right view; 34. gonoplac, left view; 35. sternum VII; 36. aedeagus, left view; 37. apex of aedeagus, ventral view; 38. male genitalia, left view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211932/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[582,614,567,591]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="38.0">38</number>
</figureCitation>
). Connective slightly thick (
<figureCitation box="[934,1073,567,591]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[199,1394,178,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1405,177,1866]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 38 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 25. male anal tube, dorsal view; 26. aedeagus, right view; 27. female anal tube, dorsal view; 28. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, ventral view; 29. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, right view; 30. capitulum, dorsal view; 31. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, dorsal view; 32. gonoplac, dorsal view; 33. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, right view; 34. gonoplac, left view; 35. sternum VII; 36. aedeagus, left view; 37. apex of aedeagus, ventral view; 38. male genitalia, left view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211932/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[998,1073,567,591]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="26.36">26, 36</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus shallowly U-shaped in lateral view, with asymmetrical process on each side of base, left process uncinate and dumpy, apex acuminate and directed caudad, right process elongate and comparatively straight, apex directed cephalad (
<figureCitation box="[1240,1423,637,661]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[199,1394,178,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1405,177,1866]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 38 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 25. male anal tube, dorsal view; 26. aedeagus, right view; 27. female anal tube, dorsal view; 28. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, ventral view; 29. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, right view; 30. capitulum, dorsal view; 31. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, dorsal view; 32. gonoplac, dorsal view; 33. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, right view; 34. gonoplac, left view; 35. sternum VII; 36. aedeagus, left view; 37. apex of aedeagus, ventral view; 38. male genitalia, left view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211932/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[1305,1378,637,661]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="26.36">26, 36</number>
, 
<number box="[1392,1423,637,661]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="37.0">37</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallobase with dorso-lateral and ventral lobes. Each dorso-lateral lobe of phallobase with apical spinous process. Ventral phallobase lobe acuminate at apex, longer than dorsolateral phallobase lobes, and strongly sclerotized. Genital style small, with concave posterior margin, caudo-ventral angle rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1080,1165,741,765]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[199,1394,178,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1405,177,1866]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 38 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 25. male anal tube, dorsal view; 26. aedeagus, right view; 27. female anal tube, dorsal view; 28. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, ventral view; 29. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, right view; 30. capitulum, dorsal view; 31. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, dorsal view; 32. gonoplac, dorsal view; 33. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, right view; 34. gonoplac, left view; 35. sternum VII; 36. aedeagus, left view; 37. apex of aedeagus, ventral view; 38. male genitalia, left view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211932/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[1134,1165,741,765]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="38.0">38</number>
</figureCitation>
). Capitulum of style, in dorsal view, with two obtuse apical processes, and large lateral tooth with apex divided into two spinules directed ventrally, a tuberculiform process under lateral teeth (
<figureCitation box="[751,836,810,834]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[199,1394,178,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1405,177,1866]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 38 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 25. male anal tube, dorsal view; 26. aedeagus, right view; 27. female anal tube, dorsal view; 28. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, ventral view; 29. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, right view; 30. capitulum, dorsal view; 31. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, dorsal view; 32. gonoplac, dorsal view; 33. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, right view; 34. gonoplac, left view; 35. sternum VII; 36. aedeagus, left view; 37. apex of aedeagus, ventral view; 38. male genitalia, left view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211932/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[804,836,810,834]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1598]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis box="[199,393,845,869]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Female genitalia</emphasis>
: Sternum VII with posterior margin clearly concave in middle (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1250,845,869]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[199,1394,178,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1405,177,1866]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 38 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 25. male anal tube, dorsal view; 26. aedeagus, right view; 27. female anal tube, dorsal view; 28. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, ventral view; 29. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, right view; 30. capitulum, dorsal view; 31. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, dorsal view; 32. gonoplac, dorsal view; 33. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, right view; 34. gonoplac, left view; 35. sternum VII; 36. aedeagus, left view; 37. apex of aedeagus, ventral view; 38. male genitalia, left view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211932/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[1220,1250,845,869]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="35.4">35</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1266,1298,845,869]" captionStart="FIGURES 39, 41" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[234,1335,192,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[234,1336,181,1952]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 39, 41 Gergithus nonomaculatus sp. nov.; 40, 42 G. tristriatus sp. nov. 39 – 40. female genitalia, ventral view; 41 – 42. general structure of the female reproductive organs, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211933/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">40</figureCitation>
). Anal tube nearly ovate in dorsal view, base wider than apex (
<figureCitation box="[742,828,879,903]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[199,1394,178,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1405,177,1866]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 38 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 25. male anal tube, dorsal view; 26. aedeagus, right view; 27. female anal tube, dorsal view; 28. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, ventral view; 29. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, right view; 30. capitulum, dorsal view; 31. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, dorsal view; 32. gonoplac, dorsal view; 33. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, right view; 34. gonoplac, left view; 35. sternum VII; 36. aedeagus, left view; 37. apex of aedeagus, ventral view; 38. male genitalia, left view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211932/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[797,828,879,903]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="27.0">27</number>
</figureCitation>
), apical margin incised (
<figureCitation box="[1114,1201,879,903]" captionStart="FIGURES 39, 41" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[234,1335,192,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[234,1336,181,1952]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 39, 41 Gergithus nonomaculatus sp. nov.; 40, 42 G. tristriatus sp. nov. 39 – 40. female genitalia, ventral view; 41 – 42. general structure of the female reproductive organs, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211933/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[1169,1201,879,903]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="40.0">40</number>
</figureCitation>
). Anal column wide (about 0.3 times as long as anal tube). Gonoplac slightly prominent medially, border between first and second gonoplac lobes obsolete, third gonoplac lobes membranous and fork strongly sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[1172,1313,949,973]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[199,1394,178,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1405,177,1866]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 38 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 25. male anal tube, dorsal view; 26. aedeagus, right view; 27. female anal tube, dorsal view; 28. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, ventral view; 29. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, right view; 30. capitulum, dorsal view; 31. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, dorsal view; 32. gonoplac, dorsal view; 33. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, right view; 34. gonoplac, left view; 35. sternum VII; 36. aedeagus, left view; 37. apex of aedeagus, ventral view; 38. male genitalia, left view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211932/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[1237,1313,949,973]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="32.34">32, 34</number>
</figureCitation>
). Proximal part of posterior connective lamina of gonapophyses IX convex in lateral view, median field with bivalvate apical part, lateral fields not projecting (
<figureCitation box="[526,662,1018,1042]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[199,1394,178,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1405,177,1866]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 38 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 25. male anal tube, dorsal view; 26. aedeagus, right view; 27. female anal tube, dorsal view; 28. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, ventral view; 29. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, right view; 30. capitulum, dorsal view; 31. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, dorsal view; 32. gonoplac, dorsal view; 33. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, right view; 34. gonoplac, left view; 35. sternum VII; 36. aedeagus, left view; 37. apex of aedeagus, ventral view; 38. male genitalia, left view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211932/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[590,662,1018,1042]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="29.31">29, 31</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxa VIII nearly rectangular, ventral margin slightly concave. Endogonocoxal process gradually narrowed to apex. Anterior connective lamina of gonapophysis VIII bearing three teeth in apical group and two teeth with carinae in lateral group (
<figureCitation box="[939,1075,1087,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[199,1394,178,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1405,177,1866]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 38 Gergithus tristriatus sp. nov. 25. male anal tube, dorsal view; 26. aedeagus, right view; 27. female anal tube, dorsal view; 28. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, ventral view; 29. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, right view; 30. capitulum, dorsal view; 31. gonapophyses IX and gonaspiculum bridge, dorsal view; 32. gonoplac, dorsal view; 33. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophysis VIII, right view; 34. gonoplac, left view; 35. sternum VII; 36. aedeagus, left view; 37. apex of aedeagus, ventral view; 38. male genitalia, left view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211932/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[1002,1075,1087,1111]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="28.33">28, 33</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1598]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis box="[199,521,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Female reproductive organs</emphasis>
: Bursa copulatrix well developed with shrinking ductus at basal half and large pouch at apical half. Posterior vagina thick, with small horseshoe-like sclerotized plate near base of bursa copulatrix ductus. Anterior vagina long and relatively thin. Oviductus communis thin and short. Spermatheca well-developed, ductus receptaculi relatively long, with elongate pouch proximally and elongated thin ductus preapically, diverticulum receptaculi distinctly dilated or bulbous with wider apical part than basal part, spermathecal pump comparatively short and acuminate with compact helix-shaped loop (Fig. 
<number box="[976,1008,1295,1319]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="42.0">42</number>
).
</paragraph>
